Agent Installation SOP
Technical Manual
How to deploy the Decision Filter Agent so it produces consistent, structured output.

Document Type: Technical Manual
Title: Agent Installation SOP
Author: AI Virtual Agency
Contact: biztechwellnessai@gmail.com
Website: www.aivirtualagency.com

Section 1 — What this SOP installs
The “agent” is not a chatbot personality. It is a repeatable workflow that always returns:
- Routing table (Green/Yellow/Red)
- Boundary rule drafts
- Escalation conditions
- Time reclaim estimate
- Summary the admin can forward

Section 2 — Required guardrails
- No shaming language
- Blame structure, not people
- Conservative estimates only
- Always provide a boundary rule when possible
- Always provide escalation criteria for Reds

Section 3 — Agent prompt structure (the operating spec)
Inputs required: Team size, Industry, Primary workflow type, Pasted “decision noise”.
Outputs required: Executive Summary, Routing Table, Boundary Rules, Reds Only escalation criteria, Time reclaim estimate, “Forward to boss” version.

Section 4 — Installation steps (how to deploy)
Step 1: Choose delivery method (Web tool, Private agent link, Embedded chat widget).
Step 2: Lock formatting (Deterministic structure).
Step 3: Test with 5 datasets (Slack, Email, Meeting notes, Approval list, Mixed).
Step 4: Add the “intentional incompleteness” for free users.

Section 5 — Admin Assistant workflow
The admin’s use case: Paste inbound chaos, Get a routing table, Send the “Reds Only” list to the decision-maker, Install Green boundaries as internal rules, Reduce follow-up chasing.

Section 6 — QA checklist (every update)
- Output order correct
- No blame language
- Always includes at least 1 boundary
- Always includes time estimate
- Free preview remains incomplete
